    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I found the problem. I need to remove <code>additivity=&quot;false&quot;</code>. Therefore having now:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;logger name=&quot;com.test.abc&quot; level=&quot;DEBUG&quot; /&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 337407,
      "reputation" : 10125,
      "user_id" : 665657,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 75,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Hje3i.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "wjans",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/665657/wjans"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1540542145,
    "creation_date" : 1540542145,
    "answer_id" : 53004475,
    "question_id" : 53003967,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>The reason why you don't see any debug logging is because your logger tag is empty, those log statements will go \"nowhere\".  And since <code>additivity=\"false\"</code> is won't be included in the root logger either.</p>\n\n<p>You can try this:</p>\n\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;configuration&gt;\n    &lt;appender name=\"STDOUT\" class=\"ch.qos.logback.core.ConsoleAppender\"&gt;\n        &lt;encoder&gt;\n            &lt;pattern&gt;%date{HH:mm:ss} %-5level [%thread] - [%logger{0}]- %msg%n&lt;/pattern&gt;\n        &lt;/encoder&gt;\n    &lt;/appender&gt;\n\n    &lt;logger name=\"com.test.abc\" level=\"DEBUG\" additivity=\"false\"&gt;\n        &lt;appender-ref ref=\"STDOUT\"/&gt;\n    &lt;/logger&gt;\n\n    &lt;root level=\"ERROR\"&gt;\n        &lt;appender-ref ref=\"STDOUT\"/&gt;\n    &lt;/root&gt;\n&lt;/configuration&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
