  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/53003967/could-logback-has-root-level-lower-than-other-loggers",
  "title" : "Could logback has root level lower than other loggers?",
  "body" : "<p>Can I have the level of <em>root</em> logger at <code>ERROR</code> and other loggers like <code>com.test.abc</code> at <code>DEBUG</code>? Why does this not work? I can do this in <code>log4j</code>.</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;configuration&gt;\n    &lt;appender name=&quot;STDOUT&quot; class=&quot;ch.qos.logback.core.ConsoleAppender&quot;&gt;\n        &lt;encoder&gt;\n            &lt;pattern&gt;%date{HH:mm:ss} %-5level [%thread] - [%logger{0}]- %msg%n&lt;/pattern&gt;\n        &lt;/encoder&gt;\n    &lt;/appender&gt;\n    &lt;logger name=&quot;com.test.abc&quot; level=&quot;DEBUG&quot; additivity=&quot;false&quot;/&gt;\n\n    &lt;root level=&quot;ERROR&quot;&gt;\n        &lt;appender-ref ref=&quot;STDOUT&quot;/&gt;\n    &lt;/root&gt;\n&lt;/configuration&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
}